<TITLE> Ex-DC, land officials gobble up acres </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com)  Land ministry officials grabbed 19 acres of abandoned and Khas land in Narayanganj in the name of a cooperative and distributed it among government officials to pocket Tk 81 lakh, the Anticorruption Commission has found. Among those who were given the land are officials from the administrative cadre starting from the deputy secretary to the secretary, judicial and military officials, wife of the district commissioner and insurance officials. At the regular news briefing on Thursday, colonel Hanif Iqbal, director general, administration, of the ACC also said that former district commissioner of Narayanganj, his subordinates and land officials were involved in the irregularity. In the name of a cooperative for officials of the land ministry, 18.66 acres of abandoned and Khas land was allotted. And later, with a 10 percent deposit, members of the cooperative were allotted lands. "As a result, the government was deprived of a revenue of Tk 81.30 lakh," said Hanif. "Despite not being members of the cooperative, officials of the Narayanganj district administration were also allotted land." He said opinions would be sought from the land ministry about actions against the corrupt civil servants. b
